\begin_layout Standard
Vector and list are part of the standard template library.
 Vector is a array with many helper functions and simple things such as
 range checking.
 List is a doubly linked list that which consists of nodes that include
 pointers to the next and previous nodes, this allows for effiencient insert
 and deletes but it doesn't allow for direct access to elements.
 Question includes the members stated above as well as a user definied copy
 constructor, copy assignment operator, and a constructor defined to take
 a input stream as an argument.
 and construct the question from a specific format.
 The best and worst case scenarios for the list and vector are identical
 when using an iterator, because we are accessing the elements in a linear
 fashion.
 If the access was non linear the vector access would be faster.
 Construction of both types in this program are also equivelent.
 If the program were to resize the list and vector, the list would be much
 more efficient.
